      "name": "FDA nozzle benchmark — velocity profile comparison",
      "description": "SST k-omega turbulence model validated against FDA nozzle experimental PIV data. Mean velocity profiles show agreement within 8% at all axial stations. Provides confidence in turbulence closure for internal rotating flow geometries."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-pump-hemolysis-multisite",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Multi-site hemolysis index validation — centrifugal pump",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against three independent laboratory measurements at 3 L/min and 5 L/min. Model predictions fall within experimental variability bands (±15%) at all operating points, supporting use of the Giersiepen power-law damage model for relative hemolysis ranking."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-mesh-independence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh independence and discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) analysis performed across three mesh refinement levels (4M, 12M, 32M cells). GCI for NIH quantity of interest is 3.2% on the fine mesh, satisfying the project threshold of <5%. Rotor-stator interface sensitivity study confirms negligible dependence on interface treatment."
    }
